<item>
            <title>[SEC-993] OpenID and RememberMe broken</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SEC-993</link>
                <project id="10040" key="SEC">Spring Security</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;m trying to create a remember-me cookie with an OpenID authentication. Since OpenIDAuthenticationToken doesn&apos;t support password, it&apos;s causing a NullPointerException in TokenBasedRememberMeServices.retrievePassword() - it calls toString() on the null password (&quot;return authentication.getCredentials().toString();&quot; line 202).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;How am I supposed to use cookies with OpenID? If I create my own RememberMeServices and leave out the password then anyone can create a cookie with my OpenID and log in as me.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
